Wash and dry all produce. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Drain and
rinse the @black beans{1%box}. Thinly slice the @radishes{3}. Zest and halve the
@lemon{1}. Finely chop the @cilantro{1/4%ounce} leaves. Halve, peel, and finely chop
the @shallot{1}.

Cook the farro: Add the @farro{3/4%cup} to the boiling water. Cook ~{20-25%minutes},
until tender. Drain and rinse it under cold water.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the lemon zest, @white wine vinegar{2%tablespoon},
shallots, cilantro, and the juice of half a lemon. Whisk in about @olive oil{2%tablespoon}.
Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Once the farro is cooked, cut the @Granny Smith apple{1} into ½-inch cubes. Halve,
pit, and cube the @avocado{1}.

Toss the farro in a #large bowl{} with the black beans and half the dressing. Serve the
black bean and farro salad with the apple, avocado, and radish slices on top. Drizzle
with as much remaining dressing as you like. Enjoy!